2026 Regular Session
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 46
BY SENATOR SEABAUGH
COMMENDATIONS. Commends John Brady on being inducted into the 2026 class of the
Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend John Brady on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports Hall
3 of Fame.
4 WHEREAS, each year the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame in Natchitoches, Louisiana
5 collaborates with the Louisiana Sports Writers Association in selecting a limited number of
6 sports figures who embody the character, skill, talent, and accomplishment worthy of being
7 named to the Hall of Fame; and
8 WHEREAS, the 2026 Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame Induction Class includes John
9 Brady; and
10 WHEREAS, Coach John Brady has enjoyed a distinguished career in collegiate
11 basketball spanning more than twenty-five seasons, during which he demonstrated
12 exceptional leadership, integrity, and dedication to the development of student-athletes; and
13 WHEREAS, a native of McComb, Mississippi, Coach Brady began his coaching
14 career in Louisiana high school basketball before advancing to the collegiate ranks, where
15 he served as the men's basketball head coach at Samford University, Arkansas State, and
16 most notably Louisiana State University; and
17 WHEREAS, over the course of his collegiate coaching career, Coach Brady compiled
18 an impressive overall record of 402 wins and 325 losses before concluding his coaching
